{"questionId":"33397549","questionHtml":"<p>Hence calculate the coordinates of the drinking fountain.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>gradient of (their) perp line<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>equation of perpendicular bisector of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AC</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>e.g. <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong><br>equation of perpendicular bisector of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>BC</mi></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong><br>equation of perpendicular bisector of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AB</mi></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>36</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> The <em><strong>A1</strong></em> is for either equation of perpendicular bisector of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>BC</mi></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AB</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>point of intersection <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>8</mn><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>10</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>67</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>10</mn></mrow></mfenced></math> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>666</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>10</mn></mrow></mfenced></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>M1</strong></em> for an attempt to equate their perpendicular bisectors</p>\n<p>Award the final <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for the correct coordinate pair – parentheses omitted or not.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[6 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33397549","referenceCode":"24M.2.SL.TZ2.2diii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Hence calculate the coordinates of the drinking fountain.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"iii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.5—Intersection of lines, equations of perpendicular bisectors"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}